begin_memory_text: We talked about our jobs a little bit and the business travel that he does. We also talked about how covid had impacted our situations from a family perspective and also from the perspective of how it impacted our kids and their schooling.
middle_memory_text: During this part we talked a lot about sports. We talked about how he was an Auburn fan and how it can be frustrating to be an Auburn fan because Alabama is such a dominant force. I talked about my relationship to Cal sports and how that is a constant gut punch. We also talked about the Dodgers a bit.
end_memory_text: At the end we talked a little bit more about baseball playoffs as well as a little bit more about his job. We also talked about this experiment and pondered what it was like for the researchers watching these tapes and if they see a lot of awkward things happen in the conversations.
rest_of_day_open: I see it as continuing to be a busy week. I have a lot going on for work currently and my wife and the kids are also busy. We are trying to juggle everything and make sure that nobody is falling behind on their tasks. We are supposed to go for a little outdoor trip this weekend and that would be fun.
critical_positive: I think that the conversation had a really nice balance and flow. He was an easy to talk with guy and the fact that we were both fans of college sports helped the conversation feel comfortable and easy. We were able to bounce around on topics and keep up with each other
critical_negative: I dont really think there was much that didnt work well during the conversation. There might have been some regional differences given his experiences of growing up in the south and living in the mid west, but even with those differences it felt like we could find a lot of common ground.

begin_memory_text: We discussed the impact of the pandemic. It led to how how that has affected work and school for kids. We also discussed our jobs and how we have worked virtually.
middle_memory_text: In the middle of the conversation we talked about sports. We discussed how we both prefer to follow collegiate sports. We both like to watch college football, though are fans for different teams.
end_memory_text: Toward the end of the conversation we continued to talk about sports. We also discussed if we had participated in this study before and what experiences we had. We discussed what we thought the study was trying to achieve.
rest_of_day_open: I see myself continuing to travel for work. This involves a forty five minute commute from a hotel. I will have nightly video calls with my spouse and daughter. On the calls I will read to my daughter. After my work week is complete, I will travel 3 hours back home. The weekend will include having family come and stay with me.
critical_positive: The main item that worked well was our willingness to have an open and friendly discussion. We both were open to finding out about each other with real interest. The genuine interest helped to make the conversation seem effortless and feel like two individuals sharing some commonalities with each other.
critical_negative: Having a video discussion made it difficult at times to tell when the other person was done talking. It allowed times for us to speak over each other. Since we are unable to read body language as you would in an in-person discussion, it becomes more difficult to determine when one person is done speaking on a topic.
